1.33.0 (const: [unstable](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/82814 "Tracking issue for const_result")) ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/result.rs.html#1632)

Transposes a `Result` of an `Option` into an `Option` of a `Result`.

`Ok(None)` will be mapped to `None`. `Ok(Some(_))` and `Err(_)` will be mapped to `Some(Ok(_))` and `Some(Err(_))`.

##### [¬ß](#examples-5)Examples

```
#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq)]
struct SomeErr;

let x: Result<Option<i32>, SomeErr> = Ok(Some(5));
let y: Option<Result<i32, SomeErr>> = Some(Ok(5));
assert_eq!(x.transpose(), y);
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++%23%5Bderive(Debug,+Eq,+PartialEq)%5D%0A++++struct+SomeErr;%0A++++%0A++++let+x:+Result%3COption%3Ci32%3E,+SomeErr%3E+=+Ok(Some(5));%0A++++let+y:+Option%3CResult%3Ci32,+SomeErr%3E%3E+=+Some(Ok(5));%0A++++assert_eq!(x.transpose(),+y);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

