Converts from `Result<Result<T, E>, E>` to `Result<T, E>`

##### [¬ß](#examples-6)Examples

```
#![feature(result_flattening)]
let x: Result<Result<&'static str, u32>, u32> = Ok(Ok("hello"));
assert_eq!(Ok("hello"), x.flatten());

let x: Result<Result<&'static str, u32>, u32> = Ok(Err(6));
assert_eq!(Err(6), x.flatten());

let x: Result<Result<&'static str, u32>, u32> = Err(6);
assert_eq!(Err(6), x.flatten());
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0A%23!%5Bfeature(result_flattening)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+x:+Result%3CResult%3C%26%27static+str,+u32%3E,+u32%3E+=+Ok(Ok(%22hello%22));%0A++++assert_eq!(Ok(%22hello%22),+x.flatten());%0A++++%0A++++let+x:+Result%3CResult%3C%26%27static+str,+u32%3E,+u32%3E+=+Ok(Err(6));%0A++++assert_eq!(Err(6),+x.flatten());%0A++++%0A++++let+x:+Result%3CResult%3C%26%27static+str,+u32%3E,+u32%3E+=+Err(6);%0A++++assert_eq!(Err(6),+x.flatten());%0A%7D&version=nightly&edition=2021)

Flattening only removes one level of nesting at a time:

```
#![feature(result_flattening)]
let x: Result<Result<Result<&'static str, u32>, u32>, u32> = Ok(Ok(Ok("hello")));
assert_eq!(Ok(Ok("hello")), x.flatten());
assert_eq!(Ok("hello"), x.flatten().flatten());
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0A%23!%5Bfeature(result_flattening)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+x:+Result%3CResult%3CResult%3C%26%27static+str,+u32%3E,+u32%3E,+u32%3E+=+Ok(Ok(Ok(%22hello%22)));%0A++++assert_eq!(Ok(Ok(%22hello%22)),+x.flatten());%0A++++assert_eq!(Ok(%22hello%22),+x.flatten().flatten());%0A%7D&version=nightly&edition=2021)

