Returns `true` if the result is [`Err`](about:blank/std/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Err "variant std::result::Result::Err") and the value inside of it matches a predicate.

##### [¬ß](#examples-3-4)Examples

```
use std::io::{Error, ErrorKind};

let x: Result<u32, Error> = Err(Error::new(ErrorKind::NotFound, "!"));
