1.16.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/iter/traits/accum.rs.html#153-155)[¬ß](#impl-Sum%3CResult%3CU,+E%3E%3E-for-Result%3CT,+E%3E)

[source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/iter/traits/accum.rs.html#175-177)[¬ß](#method.sum)

Takes each element in the [`Iterator`](../../std/iter/trait.Iterator.html "trait std::iter::Iterator"): if it is an [`Err`](about:blank/std/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Err "variant std::result::Result::Err"), no further elements are taken, and the [`Err`](about:blank/std/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Err "variant std::result::Result::Err") is returned. Should no [`Err`](about:blank/std/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Err "variant std::result::Result::Err") occur, the sum of all elements is returned.

##### [¬ß](#examples-33)Examples

This sums up every integer in a vector, rejecting the sum if a negative element is encountered:

```
let f = |&x: &i32| if x < 0 { Err("Negative element found") } else { Ok(x) };
let v = vec![1, 2];
let res: Result<i32, _> = v.iter().map(f).sum();
assert_eq!(res, Ok(3));
let v = vec![1, -2];
let res: Result<i32, _> = v.iter().map(f).sum();
assert_eq!(res, Err("Negative element found"));
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+f+=+%7C%26x:+%26i32%7C+if+x+%3C+0+%7B+Err(%22Negative+element+found%22)+%7D+else+%7B+Ok(x)+%7D;%0A++++let+v+=+vec!%5B1,+2%5D;%0A++++let+res:+Result%3Ci32,+_%3E+=+v.iter().map(f).sum();%0A++++assert_eq!(res,+Ok(3));%0A++++let+v+=+vec!%5B1,+-2%5D;%0A++++let+res:+Result%3Ci32,+_%3E+=+v.iter().map(f).sum();%0A++++assert_eq!(res,+Err(%22Negative+element+found%22));%0A%7D&edition=2021)

